What is an Arrow Function?

Arrow functions are a modern and shorter way to write functions in JavaScript.

Normal Function vs Arrow Function
Normal Function
function greet() {
    console.log("Hello");
}
Arrow Function
const greet = () => {
    console.log("Hello");
};

Both work the same.

Arrow Function Syntax
const functionName = () => {
    // code
};
Arrow Function Example
const sayHi = () => {
    console.log("Hi Atharv");
};

sayHi();

Output:

Hi Atharv
Arrow Function with Parameters
const greet = (name) => {
    console.log("Hello " + name);
};

greet("Atharv");

Output:

Hello Atharv
Arrow Function with Multiple Parameters
const add = (a, b) => {
    console.log(a + b);
};

add(10, 5);

Output:

15
